His past history has included the following diagnoses:
1) Status-post endovascular repair, asymptomatic abdominal aneurysm, complicated with a small type II endo vascular leak.
2) Microscopic hematuria (evaluation negative except for a small intrarenal calculus).
3) Negative exercise stress sestamibi for coronary ischemia (2004).
4) Multiple bilateral subcentimeter pulmonary nodules on CT scanning (no change after one-year).
5) Hypertriglyceridemia and hypoalphalipoproteinemia consistent with metabolic syndrome.
6) Hypertension.
7) Aortic valve sclerosis without stenosis and normal LV size and systolic and diastolic function on echocardiography 2003.
8) Diabetes mellitus, Type II.
9) Negative exercise sestamibi for ischemia, double product 22,352 on Bruce protocol 7 minutes, no angina.
10) Colonoscopy 2005 done at-home.
11) Asymptomatic hyperuricemia.
12) Elevated liver transaminase, most likely secondary to fatty infiltration of the liver (NASH syndrome) with previously negative hepatitis profile and iron studies.
13) Overweight.
14) Paroxysmal atrial fibrillation currently well-controlled on Rythmol.
15) Probable mild obstructive sleep apnea with previously mildly abnormal overnight.
16) Mild hypercalcemia with low-normal PTH levels, currently on low-dose hydrochlorothiazide.

